COMPLETE EKS + IAM CLEANUP COMMANDS (COPY THIS)
🔹 1️⃣ Check Existing EKS Clusters
aws eks list-clusters --region us-east-1
🔹 2️⃣ If Cluster Exists – List Node Groups

Replace <cluster-name> with your cluster name.

aws eks list-nodegroups \
  --cluster-name <cluster-name> \
  --region us-east-1
🔹 3️⃣ Delete Node Group (VERY IMPORTANT FIRST)

Replace <cluster-name> and <nodegroup-name>

aws eks delete-nodegroup \
  --cluster-name <cluster-name> \
  --nodegroup-name <nodegroup-name> \
  --region us-east-1

Wait until status becomes DELETED

Check status:

aws eks describe-nodegroup \
  --cluster-name <cluster-name> \
  --nodegroup-name <nodegroup-name> \
  --region us-east-1
🔹 4️⃣ Delete EKS Cluster
aws eks delete-cluster \
  --name <cluster-name> \
  --region us-east-1

Verify:

aws eks list-clusters --region us-east-1
🔥 IAM ROLE CLEANUP
🔹 5️⃣ Check IAM Roles
aws iam list-roles | grep eks
🔹 6️⃣ Detach Cluster Role Policy
aws iam list-attached-role-policies \
  --role-name eks-cluster-cloud

Detach:

aws iam detach-role-policy \
  --role-name eks-cluster-cloud \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEKSClusterPolicy

Delete role:

aws iam delete-role \
  --role-name eks-cluster-cloud
🔹 7️⃣ Detach Node Group Role Policies

Check attached policies:

aws iam list-attached-role-policies \
  --role-name eks-node-group-cloud

Detach all three (run all):

aws iam detach-role-policy \
  --role-name eks-node-group-cloud \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEKSWorkerNodePolicy
aws iam detach-role-policy \
  --role-name eks-node-group-cloud \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEC2ContainerRegistryReadOnly
aws iam detach-role-policy \
  --role-name eks-node-group-cloud \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AmazonEKS_CNI_Policy

Now delete role:

aws iam delete-role \
  --role-name eks-node-group-cloud
🔹 8️⃣ Final Verification
aws iam list-roles | grep eks
aws eks list-clusters --region us-east-1

If nothing prints → ✅ Everything Deleted Successfully

🚀 After Cleanup – Run Terraform Fresh

Go to your Terraform folder:

terraform init
terraform apply
💡 VERY IMPORTANT (DevOps Real Practice)

Before deleting project folder or EC2:

Always run:

terraform destroy

Better approach:

Use S3 backend

Use DynamoDB locking

Never delete terraform.tfstate manually


